at is surprising is that we make so many genders from oak?\r\n\r\nThe Caucasus is a region of Russia, famous for its forests. Oaks grow here in abundance. And here, in the Caucasus, is our factory, on which the wood of these oaks is transformed into billets for the further production of parquet. Due to the territorial proximity, we can visit suppliers at any time to make sure that the forestry is conducted in accordance with the principles of sustainable development.','Mighty Oak','','publish','closed','closed','','51','','','2018-12-12 18:42:12','2018-12-12 17:42:12','',0,'http://oakwoodtimber.com/?post_type=oakwood_post&#038;p=51',0,'oakwood_post','',0),(52,1,'2018-11-06 02:34:26','2018-11-06 01:34:26','','mighty-oak','','inherit','open','closed','','blog_1','','','2018-11-06 02:34:44','2018-11-06 01:34:44','',51,'http://oakwoodtimber.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/blog_1.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(53,1,'2018-11-08 02:47:31','2018-11-08 01:47:31','Parquet flooring - a beautiful decoration of any living space; it is always prestige and durability. People prefer the tree for its qualities such as the newest production technologies, the characteristics of wood species, a lot of ways of laying limitlessly expand the decorative possibilities of the parquet. But remember, this material is live, it\'s not a tile \"put and forgotten\". Regular maintenance of the parquet is extremely important.\r\n\r\n<b>Care instructions:</b>\r\n1. rollers of chairs and chairs (if any) must be special, unable to damage the coating;\r\n2. wipe the floors with a soft cotton cloth, clean with a normal vacuum cleaner or a hair brush;\r\n3. Do not use abrasive materials during cleaning;\r\n4. If you have animals in your house, make sure that their claws are always cut, and they do not bring mud into their homes;\r\n5. It is also unacceptable to use hard objects - this will inevitably damage the layer of varnish: as a result, mud and moisture will penetrate into the tree;\r\n6. It is possible to effectively get rid of pollution with the help of special tools - the so-called \"clinics\". Their uniqueness lies in chemical neutrality with respect to lacquer. All major manufacturers of parquet chemistry have in their assortment similar means.\r\n7. It is necessary to perform thorough manual or machine cleaning of parquet floors only on \"serious indications\": if there are strong, cured impurities that do not disappear in the usual way;\r\n8. in the rooms where parquet is laid, it is necessary to maintain a constant level of humidity corresponding to the type of boards used - for this purpose it is best to use humidification and conditioning systems;\r\n9. in places with high humidity - for example, near the sink, washing machine and dishwasher, it is better to use protective decorative mats. The same solution is also relevant for places with the greatest load, which are subject to rapid wear.\r\n<h2>Temperature and humidity level:</h2>\r\nOptimal for any parquet is the average room temperature from 18 to 25 degrees. Overheating parquet is extremely undesirable. At the same time, perhaps even more important is the humidity of the air, since the porous structure of the wood is active, as it absorbs moisture at its excess, and it shrinks and starts to creak, with its lack.\r\n\r\nRecommended air humidity in rooms with parquet floors: 40-60%. In winter, when the heating season starts, humidity often drops to 20%, which can cause the parquet to crack. In such cases, it is recommended to wipe the floors with a damp cloth more often, use humidifiers. Indoor plants and aquariums are also natural regulators of the microclimate and moisture regime.','Lacquered parquet, care rules.','','publish','closed','closed','','lacquered-parquet-care-rules','','','2018-12-12 11:19:45','2018-12-12 10:19:45','',0,'http://oakwoodtimber.com/?post_type=oakwood_post&#038;p=53',0,'oakwood_post','',0),(54,1,'2018-11-06 02:47:11','2018-11-06 01:47:11','','parquet care rules','','inherit','open','closed','','blog_2','','','2018-12-12 15:29:55','2018-12-12 14:29:55','',53,'http://oakwoodtimber.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/blog_2.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(55,1,'2018-11-06 02:48:27','2018-11-06 01:48:27','<h2>If there are scratches on the parquet floor?</h2>\r\nMost of all, the wooden floor suffers from external influences: sand, pebbles, heels, - all this can very quickly turn your floor into disrepair. The best way to care for parquet floors is to prevent damage, but if minor scratches do appear, you can eliminate this defect yourself. To do this, you can use a special restoring paste, designed for cosmetic repair of parquet floors. Paste the spatula on the parquet, while the surplus material should be removed immediately. With deeper and numerous damages, the output is one: grinding and re-coating with varnish.\r\n<h2>If the parquet changed color?</h2>\r\nIt should be noted that different wood species react differently to ultraviolet radiation. Regardless of the chosen coating (varnish or oil), the shade of wood will change slightly when the tree is fully ripe. The rate of maturation depends on the species of the tree, for example, cherry, darkens faster than the rest. To ensure that the floors do not change color, do not lay carpets on the floor for the first time after laying the parquet, if possible, protect from excess moisture and direct sunlight.\r\n<h2>If the parquet laths are swollen?</h2>\r\nCauses of swelling of parquet laths can be different: from high humidity to insufficiently wide gap between the dies. Moisture can accumulate under the lacquered surface, resulting in swelling. To avoid such problems, it is important to leave a sufficient gap initially. The end connections in the row should be shifted by about 50 cm. In new buildings, under the parquet should be laid moisture-proof insulation','Elimination of defects and damages','','publish','closed','closed','','55','','','2018-11-16 17:21:46','2018-11-16 16:21:46','',0,'http://oakwoodtimber.com/?post_type=oakwood_post&#038;p=55',0,'oakwood_post','',0),(56,1,'2018-11-06 02:48:11','2018-11-06 01:48:11','','Elimination of defects and damages','','inherit','open','closed','','blog_3','','','2018-12-12 15:30:14','2018-12-12 14:30:14','',55,'http://oakwoodtimber.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/11/blog_3.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(120,1,'2018-11-08 14:47:03','2018-11-08 13:47:03','','Products','','publish','closed','closed','','products','','','2018-11-23 13:11:31','2018-11-23 12:11:31','',0,'http://oakwoodtimber.com/?p=120',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(59,1,'2018-11-06 10:27:50','2018-11-06 09:27:50','.scrollup{\n	display: none;\n}\n#colophon{\n	display: none;\n}','oakwood','','inherit','closed','closed','','31-revision-v1','','','2018-11-06 10:27:50','2018-11-06 09:27:50','',31,'http://oakwoodtimber.com/?p=59',0,'revision','',0),(73,1,'2018-11-06 12:48:14','2018-11-06 11:48:14','<div class=\"col-md-12\">\r\n\r\n<b>Company name:</b> Dubové podlahy s.r.o.\r\n\r\n<b>Based in:</b> Czech republic, Prague 10, ZIP 19000, náměstí Přátelství 1518/2, Hostivař\r\n\r\n<b>Identification number:</b> 242 92 206\r\n\r\n<b>Tax identification number:</b> CZ 242 92 206\r\n\r\n<b>Internet portal:</b><a href=\"http://oakwoodtimber.com/\"> http://oakwoodtimber.com/</a>\r\n\r\n<b>e-mail:</b> <a href=\"mailto:dubpodlahy@gmail.com\">dubpodlahy@gmail.com</a>\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"ol-count col-md-12\">\r\n\r\n(hereinafter the „Seller“)\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>\r\n<h3>Complaints and Returns</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>The warranty conditions for goods are governed by applicable laws.</li>\r\n 	<li>Buyer is required to view the goods immediately after handing over and picking up at the Seller’s warehouse or at the destination. Deviations of the delivered goods from the confirmed order which are observable from the accompanying documents and the marking of the goods and obvious defects, the Buyer shall be obliged to claim immediately, but not later than within